gnome-pilot: gnome-pilot (GNOME Pilot Manager)
gnome-pilot:
gnome-pilot: Gnome-Pilot is a package with a daemon (gpilotd) that monitor for
gnome-pilot: pilot connects on one or more devices (cradles/XCopilots/xxx). It has
gnome-pilot: an API for creating conduits as well as a couple of default conduits,
gnome-pilot: including one for backing up files, and one for installing files.
gnome-pilot: 
gnome-pilot: Other packages exist that provide additional conduits, most notably
gnome-pilot: gnome-pilot-conduits, and the Evolution mail/calendar/memo PIM
gnome-pilot: application suite.

